<HEADLINE>
DETROIT: the third.
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Bruins 3, Sharks 0 &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   In San Jose, California, goaltender Robbie Tallas turned back 22
shots as the Boston Bruins beat San Jose, spoiling the Sharks' home
opener.
	   Peter Ferraro, Sergei Samsonov and Dmitri Khristich each had
goals for the Bruins, who improved their lifetime record against
the Sharks to 9-1-3 with a 53-33 scoring advantage in those games.
	   Tallas, starting in place of regular goaltender Byron Dafoe,
registered his third career shutout in his first appearance of the
season. It was the third victory by shutout in five games this
season for the Bruins.
