<SLUG> BC-Malaysia-Boat Capsize, 1st Ld-Writethru </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Fifteen feared drowned after Malaysian boat capsizes
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: UPDATES throughout with details of rescue and bodies
recovered; one name correct for Suraya in 4th graf &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   KUALA LUMPUR, Malaysia (AP) _ Rescuers retrieved five bodies
Monday from the choppy seas off Malaysia's western coast and said
10 other people were still missing after a passenger boat capsized,
the national news agency reported.
	   Sixteen others on the boat, which was carrying mostly workers
from a holiday resort on Pulau Besar island to the mainland, swam
to safety when the vessel sank around midnight Sunday, Bernama news
agency said.
	   The area is about 200 kilometers (125 miles) from the capital,
Kuala Lumpur.
	   Of the bodies recovered, two were of men and three of women.
Police identified two as being those of Hazimah Harun and Suraya,
both employees at the Bandar Nusa Island Resort in Pulau Besar. The
other three were yet to be identified, police said.
	   Divers from the police and fire department were trying to locate
the capsized boat. They feared passengers may be trapped inside it.
	   Among the missing were nine men, including the captain of the
boat, and six women, Bernama reported.
	   The cause of the disaster was not immediately known, but the
boat reportedly sank in rough seas. 	   
</TEXT>
