<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Russia-Hostage </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Russian soldier released from Chechen captivity
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MOSCOW (AP) _ A Russian soldier captured this summer and taken
to the breakaway republic of Chechnya has been released in an
exchange for a Chechen convict in Russia, a news report said
Monday.
	   Capt. Medzhid Kurbanov was handed over to Russian officials
Sunday in Dagestan, which borders Chechnya. He was in such poor
condition after two months in captivity that he had difficulty
recognizing his own father, the ITAR-Tass news agency reported.
	   There were no details about the Chechen convict who was
released.
	   Kidnappers have taken hundreds of people hostage in Chechnya and
surrounding areas, usually for ransom, since the region's two-year
war for independence from Russia ended in 1996. Chechnya runs its
own affairs, but Moscow still considers it part of Russia.
	   (nw/gm) 	   
</TEXT>
