Economic Cooperation forum prepares for its November summit in
Malaysia. ASIA-COMPLICATIONS. Expected by 0700 GMT. By Thomas
Wagner.
	   ANKARA, Turkey _ High-ranking officials from Turkey and Syria
will meet Monday at a secret location to hold security talks aimed
at easing tensions between the neighbors, foreign ministry
officials confirm. TURKEY-SYRIA. Has moved.
	   TEHRAN, Iran _ Thousands of pro-democracy demonstrators rally in
a Tehran park to protest the rejection of scores of candidates for
the election of a powerful assembly. IRAN-RALLY. Has moved. By
Scheherezade Faramarzi.
	   SKOPJE, Macedonia _ After campaigns focused on Macedonia's
economic woes, voters in the first round of parliamentary elections
choose between incumbents who led the country peacefully to
independence from Yugoslavia or a team of younger politicians.
MACEDONIA-ELECTIONS. Has moved; developments will be expedited.
First official results expected later Monday. By Konstantin
Testorides. AP Photos SKO101-107.
	   WASHINGTON _ Microsoft Corp., facing a landmark antitrust trial
Monday, is depicted by government lawyers as an aggressive predator
that jealously and illegally protects its dominance in the
technology industry. The company contends it acted in the interests
of consumers and technical benefit. US-MICROSOFT. Expected by 0800
GMT. Lead expected with start of trial at 1400 GMT. By Ted Bridis.
AP Photo NY108.
	   BONN, Germany _ Having agreed to shift German politics to the
left, Social Democrats and Greens haggle Monday about whom to put
in charge of the changes. GERMANY-POLITICS. Has moved. Talks to
start at 1500 GMT. By Tony Czuczka.
	   ALSO:
	   _GERMANY-AUTOBAHN CULTURE _ Law of the jungle rules the autobahn
_ and Germans like it. Has moved. By Paul Geitner.
	   VATICAN CITY _ Pope John Paul II reflects on his 20 years as
pontiff and wonders aloud how well he has served the church and
what he called the world's longing for truth. POPE-ANNIVERSARY. Has
moved. By Frances D'Emilio. AP Photos ROM101-102,106-9,111.
	   LOOKING AHEAD: On Monday, an IMF mission arrives in Moscow to
discuss possible additional loan installments. On Wednesday,
diplomats from North and South Korea, the United States and China
open a new round of talks in Geneva, Switzerland.
 &UR; FEATURES:
	    &UR; NEW:
	   DHAKA, Bangladesh _ Author Taslima Nasrin fled her homeland four
years ago because of protests that erupted after a newspaper quoted
her as saying Islam's holy book should be rewritten. Ending her
self-exile in September, Nasrin came home to be with her
60-year-old mother, who has colon cancer. She has had to remain in
hiding ever since. FEA-BANGLADESH-AUTHOR UNDER FIRE. Expected by
0700 GMT. By Farid Hossain. AP Photo NY110.
