<HEADLINE>
With BC-FEA-Bangladesh-Author Under Fire
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; By The Associated Press &QC; 

<TEXT>
	   Excerpts from writings of Taslima Nasrin:
	   ___
	   ``In our country, the universities make it mandatory for women
to return to their dormitories before sunset. The rule does not
apply to the male students. They treat the girls as if they are
domestic animals. All the restrictions are only for women. It
shocks me to find that women are considered as commodities _ good
only for pleasure and enjoyment of men.''
	   From ``Nirbachito Column,'' a compilation of newspaper essays.
	   ___
	   ``Neither religion nor state has given women the dignity they
deserve. Religion has created most of disparities between men and
women. According to the Koran, women must confine themselves to
home. The world outside is not for them.''
	   From ``Nirbachito Column.''
	   ___
	   ``You're a girl
	   when you keep on walking down the lane
	   men will follow you and whistle.
	   When you cross the lane and step onto the main road
	   men will revile you and call you a loose woman.''
	   The poem ``Character.''
	   ___
	   ``A pack of dogs is after you
	   Remember, rabies.
	   A pack of men is after you,
	   Remember, syphilis.''
	   The poem ``Run!''
</TEXT>
