<SLUG> BC-Russia-Yeltsin </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Yeltsin cancels meetings Monday, still recovering from cold
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MOSCOW (AP) _ Russian President Boris Yeltsin canceled meetings
with senior leaders Monday because he is still recovering from a
cold, a news report said.
	   The president is feeling the lingering effects of a respiratory
infection, but his health is ``satisfactory,'' said presidential
spokesman Dmitry Yakushin, according to the Interfax news agency.
	   Yeltsin had been scheduled to meet Prime Minister Yevgeny
Primakov and Boris Pastukhov, the minister in charge of relations
with the former Soviet republics.
	   The president's latest illness forced him to cut short a visit
to Central Asia last week, and he spent most of the week at a
country residence outside Moscow. The president also has canceled a
trip to Malaysia for a summit next month.
	   According to Yeltsin's office, the president will return to work
in the Kremlin on Tuesday, where he will meet with Primakov and
other officials.
	   Yeltsin has been plagued by recurring health problems in recent
years. He had heart bypass surgery two years ago, and has made
fewer and fewer public appearances since then. Each new ailment
rekindles speculation about his fitness to govern.
	   The president and his doctors say Yeltsin has no serious health
problems and will serve out the final two years of his term.
	   (nw/gm) 	   
</TEXT>
