<HEADLINE>
Fire kills two soldiers in Russian Far East
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MOSCOW (AP) _ Fire that gutted an army barracks in Russia's Far
East killed two soldiers, a news report said Monday.
	   The two soldiers in Yuzhno-Sakhalinsk were killed when fire
engulfed their barracks late Sunday night, the ITAR-Tass news
agency reported.
	   Firefighters were called in to battle the blaze, but could not
control it and the entire barracks burned down.
	   Yuzhno-Sakhalinsk is the capital of Sakhalin Island, located off
Russia's Pacific coast. The region has been plagued by forest fires
in recent months.
