<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Philippines-Cardinal Sin </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Cardinal Sin to stay longer in hospital due to fever
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MANILA, Philippines (AP) _ Manila's influential Roman Catholic
archbishop, Jaime Cardinal Sin has developed pneumonia while in the
hospital and will have to remain there a while longer, his
spokesman said Monday.
	   Msgr. Socrates Villegas said the 70-year-old prelate ``developed
a pulmonary congestion due to his disposition to retain fluids in
his body.''
	   Villegas said Sin continues to undergo regular dialysis due to
renal problems and doctors are monitoring his condition.
	   Sin was hospitalized Sept. 28 with fever and stomach pains after
a tube inserted in his peritoneum, the membrane lining the
abdominal cavity, apparently introduced bacteria into his system,
church officials said.
	   Sin helped bring about the ouster of strongman Ferdinand Marcos
in 1986 when he called for citizens to support a military revolt
against the president. Hundreds of thousands of people rallied in
the streets, forcing Marcos from power.
	   He continues to be heavily involved in political and social
issues in the Philippines, Asia's only predominantly Catholic
country. 	   
</TEXT>
