 &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  APTN'S 0600 OUTLOOK FOR MONDAY 19 OCTOBER 1998 &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC; 
----
For Planner/Newsdesk use - stories expected to move in the next 12
hours. All times in GMT.
----
EXPECTED: &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC; 
----
NIGERIA: FIRE - At least 250 people were reported killed after
thieves siphoning off oil apparently sparked a pipeline blast that
led to an inferno. The raging fire destroyed villages and charred
surrounding cropland near the town of Jesse, 180 miles southeast of
Lagos. APTN is efforting coverage. (TIMING TO BE CONFIRMED)
----
JAPAN: MAHATHIR 2 - Coverage of Malaysian Prime Minister Mahathir
Mohamad meeting his Japanese counterpart Keizo Obuchi. (EXPECTED
AFTER 1000)
----
UK: NIRELAND - Prime Minister Tony Blair will have separate talks
with Northern Ireland First Minister David Trimble and Sinn Fein's
Martin McGuinness on Monday in an attempt to resolve the arms
decommissioning crisis which threatens the Northern Ireland peace
process. APTN will cover. (EXPECTED AFTER 0900)
----
CHINA: WEDDING - At a time when the government is considering
controversial proposals to strengthen marriage, almost 400 couples
exchanged their vows at a mass wedding ceremony in Shanghai. APTN
has the story. (FIRST RUN 0715 ASIA PACIFIC)
----
HK: TOURISM - Government statistics show that tourism figures have
risen to the highest level for over a year. However, the increase in
the number of visitors to the region is largely explained by a
relaxing in the restrictions on mainland Chinese visitors. APTN's
feature includes footage of Chinese tour groups going round Hong
Kong and comment from an analyst. (FIRST RUN 0715 ASIA PACIFIC LATE)
----
US: MICROSOFT - The U-S Justice Department takes on Microsoft on
Monday for a legal fight that may have repercussions for anyone who
uses a personal computer (P-C).
APTN has a preview. (FIRST RUN 0715 ASIA PACIFIC LATE)
----
CHINA: VIETNAM - Coverage of Vietnamese Prime Minister Phan Van
Khai's state visit, including of his meeting with his Chinese
counterpart Zhu Rongji. It's the first visit by a Vietnamese prime
minister since 1991 when the two countries normalized their
diplomatic relations. (EXPECTED AFTER 1045)
----
RUNNING: &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC; 
----
US/KOSOVO: WRAP - Coverage of more members of an advance team of an
expected two-thousand unarmed international monitors arriving in
Kosovo plus comments from U-S envoy Richard Holbrooke on the Kosovo
crisis. (WRAP FIRST RUN 0300 EUROPE)
----
US: MIDEAST WRAP 2 - The Middle East peace negotiations remained
stalled over key elements of a land-for-peace deal between Israel
and the Palestinians, but the U-S said talks would "almost
certainly" continue on Monday. APTN's package includes stills of
President Clinton meeting the two delegations and comments from
State Department spokesman James Rubin. (FIRST RUN 0000
AUSTRALIA/NZ)
----
PINOCHET: WRAP - The arrest in a London hospital of General Augusto
Pinochet sparked demonstrations for and against him in both Britain
and Chile on Sunday. APTN has coverage of an anti-Pinochet rally
outside the clinic where the former dictator is undergoing medical
treatment, footage of a protest rally in Santiago outside the
British embassy, comments from the Spanish prime minister, Chilean
politicians and from the son of Orlando Letelier, Chile's former
chancellor who was allegedly assassinated under Pinochet's orders.
(WRAP FIRST RUN 0300 EUROPE EARLY)
----
RUSSIA: ECOLOGY - As the country suffers a crippling financial
crisis, the environment is coming under increasing pressure with
"green" concerns falling by the wayside as struggling industries and
individuals focus all of their energies on just getting by. APTN
reports from the industrial regions Norilsk and Kemerovo. (FIRST RUN
0300 EUROPE)
----
COLOMBIA: BLAST - At least 45 people were killed after a pipeline
explosion and fire in the tiny village of Machuca, reportedly the
result of an attack by leftist rebels. APTN has aftermath coverage,
including footage of the injured being treated on the scene and
being flown to nearby hospitals. (FIRST RUN 2250 F-L-A-S-H)
----
EGYPT: CRASH 2 - At least 47 people were killed on Sunday when a
train jumped its tracks at the station of Kafr el-Dawar and careened
across the platform. The package includes coverage of the rescue
operation, comments from eye witnesses and hospital scenes. (WRAP
FIRST RUN 0300 EUROPE EARLY)
----
PORTUGAL: SUMMIT - Leaders at the Ibero-American summit on Sunday
urged the world's industrial powers to take urgent action to end the
world's economic
recession, warning that their countries were the world's last line
of defense against "a grave global recession". They also discussed
the border conflict between Peru and Ecuador and other regional
issues. (FIRST RUN LATIN AMERICA 2130)
----
JAPAN: MAHATHIR - Malaysian Prime Minister Mahathir Mohamad
indirectly criticized his close neighbors Indonesia and the
Philippines during his speech at the Tokyo International Conference
on African Development, which is hosted by the Japanese government.
(FIRST RUN 0300 EUROPE EARLY)
----
TEXAS: FLOODS - At least 14 people are known to have died in
widespread flooding which hit Texas over the weekend. APTN has flood
coverage from across the U-S state. (FIRST RUN 0300 EUROPE EARLY)
----
ESALVADOR: MIDWIVES - Pregnancy remains the number one killer in El
Salvador for women able to conceive - due to lack of medical help,
health and education. APTN has a special report on how aid workers
are reaching out to the country's poorest rural communities in a bid
to reduce the high mortality rate among mothers to be. (FIRST RUN
1440 APTV EUROVISION)
----
US: SOSA - New York's Dominican community gave Chicago Cubs baseball
slugger Sammy Sosa a hero's welcome on Sunday. (FIRST RUN 2250
F-L-A-S-H)
----
