w1249 &Cx1f; wstm-
r i &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-Romania-Ceausescu     10-19 0151
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Romania-Ceausescu </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Socialists use former Communist dictator as election gimmick
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   BUCHAREST, Romania (AP) _ Nicolae Ceausescu's smiling face has
sprung up around Bucharest again.
	   The Romanian Worker Party is using a poster of the former
Communist dictator to woo voters in the city's Oct. 25 mayoral
elections.
	   ``Remember all I did for the Romanian people,'' reads the
nostalgic message. ``If you are sorry I am gone, vote for Romanian
Worker Party candidate.''
	   Gherghina Dima, one of 20 candidates running for mayor says she
hopes the idea will catch on with voters.
	   People have gotten poorer in recent years as Romania struggles
to retool its economy along market lines. Purchasing power is down
and the average monthly salary is 1.2 million lei (dlrs 128).
	   ``They shot me. Do you live any better?'' asks Ceausescu smiling
in a propaganda pose.
	   (mc/am/rr)
</TEXT>
