<SLUG> BC-Hungary-Illegal Aliens </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Romanians caught at Hungary's border
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   BUDAPEST, Hungary (AP) _ Fifty-eight Romanians were found in two
trucks trying to illegally enter into Hungary, a newspaper said
Monday.
	   The incident occurred at Nagylak, 280 kilometers (200 miles)
southeast of Budapest, on Saturday, when border guards officials
opened a truck carrying rattan to Italy, Nepszabadsag quoted border
guards spokesman, Agoston Wentzel as saying.
	   The Romanians paid dlrs 500-900 to the human smugglers, they
told Hungarian authorities.
	   The border violators will soon be extradited to Romania.
	   (ek)
</TEXT>
