<SLUG> BC-Sports-Tennis-Czech Indoor </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Top seeded Korda toppled by Safin in the first round
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   OSTRAVA, Czech Republic (AP) - Russian junior Marat Safin
crushed top-seeded Petr Korda of the Czech Republic 6-4, 6-2 Monday
in the first round of the dlrs 1 million IPB Czech Indoor tennis
tournament.
	   Korda started the match with several unforced errors and soon
lost his serve to the 18-year-old Russian. Safin gained a 3-1 lead
and comfortably won the first set, capitalizing on his powerful
serve and clever play on the net.
	   Safin waisted no time with Korda in the second set, beating him
in less than 30 minutes.
	   The Australian Open Champion, who is 9th in ATP rankings this
year, lost his third consecutive first-round match in an ATP event
and has now little chance to qualify for the ATP World Championship
in Hannover.
	   In a match of poweful baseliners, seventh-seed Thomas Enquist of
Sweden had the stronger nerves and better concentration to outplay
doubles specialist Paul Haarhuis of the Netherlands 3-6, 6-4, 6-4
after almost two hours.
	   Also Monday, eighth-seed Thomas Johansson of Sweden beat
Australian Andrew Ilie 6-4, 6-4, France's Guillaume Raoux defeated
Mikael Tillstroem of Sweden 4-6, 6-3, 7-6 (7-3), home-crowd
favorite Jiri Novak rallied to beat wild card holder Nicolas Kiefer
of Germany 7-6 (7-5), 0-6, 7-6 (7-2) and Wayne Black of Zimbabwe
overpowered Radek Stepanek of the Czech Republic 6-3, 6-3.
	   The tournament's favorite, second seed Andre Agassi of the
United States, is scheduled to play his first-round match against
Denmark's Kenneth Carlsen Wednesday.
	   (js/rp)	   
</TEXT>
