<HEADLINE>
Tyson get boxing license back
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; URGENT &QL; 
 &UR; Eds: Leads throughout to commission restoring license &QL; 
 &UR; By TIM DAHLBERG &QC; 
 &UR; AP Sports Writer &QC; 

<TEXT>
	   LAS VEGAS (AP) _ Mike Tyson was given his boxing license back
Monday after pleading with officials to stop ``torturing'' him and
allow him to return to the sport he once dominated.
	   Tyson told the Nevada Athletic Commission that he has suffered
enough for biting Evander Holyfield's ears during a title fight
last year and that he needs to box to make a living.
	   Chairman Elias Ghanem said Tyson had made many mistakes in his
life but deserved another chance. The commission voted 4-1 to
restore the fighter's license.
	   Tyson was near tears when he heard that he could return to the
ring, as his supporters hugged him and patted on his back.
	    &UR; MORE
</TEXT>
