<SLUG> BC-Sports-Tennis-Czech Indoor,0242 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Top-seeded Korda upset by Safin in first round
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   OSTRAVA, Czech Republic (AP) _ Russian junior Marat Safin upset
top-seeded Petr Korda of the Czech Republic 6-4, 6-2 Monday in the
first round of the dlrs 1 million Czech Indoor tournament.
	   Korda started the match with several unforced errors and soon
lost his serve to the 18-year-old Safin.
	   Safin gained a 3-1 lead and easily won the first set,
capitalizing on his powerful serve and clever play at the net.
	   Safin wasted no time in the second set, beating Korda in less
than 30 minutes.
	   The Australian Open champion, who is ranked ninth in the world,
lost his third consecutive first-round match in an ATP event and
now has little chance to qualify for the ATP World Championship at
Hanover, Germany.
	   In a match of powerful baseliners, seventh-seeded Thomas Enquist
of Sweden beat doubles specialist Paul Haarhuis of the Netherlands
3-6, 6-4, 6-4.
	   Also, eighth-seeded Thomas Johansson of Sweden beat Australian
Andrew Ilie 6-4, 6-4, France's Guillaume Raoux defeated Mikael
Tillstrom of Sweden 4-6, 6-3, 7-6 (7-3), home-crowd favorite Jiri
Novak rallied to beat wild card Nicolas Kiefer of Germany 7-6
(7-5), 0-6, 7-6 (7-2), and Wayne Black of Zimbabwe overpowered
Radek Stepanek of the Czech Republic 6-3, 6-3.
	   Second-seeded Andre Agassi plays his first-round match against
Denmark's Kenneth Carlsen Wednesday.
</TEXT>
