<HEADLINE>
Parliament speaker's aide comes out of coma after shooting
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MOSCOW (AP) _ An aide to the speaker of Russia's lower house of
parliament regained consciousness Monday three days after he was
shot in the head by an unidentified gunman, doctors said.
	   Mikhail Osherov remained in serious condition, the Interfax news
agency quoted Igor Yakovenko, chief doctor at the Polyenov
Neurosurgery Institute in St. Petersburg as saying.
	   ``Despite a certain improvement in his condition, it is out of
the question for investigators to be allowed to record his
evidence,'' Yakovenko said.
	   Osherov, an aide to Gennady Seleznyov, the speaker of the State
Duma. was hit while he was walking into his apartment building
Friday.
	   Police said Monday they had made no arrests in the case.
	   Many Russian businessmen acquire credentials as legislative
aides in hopes that would help advance their business interests,
and many have fallen victim to contract murders. It was unclear
whether Osherov had any business connections.
	   (adc)
