<SLUG> BC-Russia-Greece </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Greek foreign minister to visit Moscow
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MOSCOW (AP) _ The Greek foreign minister will visit Russia this
week for talks on Kosovo and the divided island of Cyprus, a news
report said Monday.
	   Theodoros Pangalos is scheduled to be in Moscow from Wednesday
through Friday, and will meet Russian Foreign Minister Igor Ivanov
on Thursday, the Interfax news agency quoted the Russian Foreign
Ministry as saying.
	   The ministry said Pangalos' talks would not address military
cooperation between the two countries.
	   Russia has delayed delivery of S-300 anti-aircraft missiles to
Greek-controlled Cyprus for several months because of threats from
Turkey of conflict on the divided island.
	   Russia fiercely opposes proposed NATO airstrikes on the Yugoslav
province of Kosovo, and Pangalos has said Western powers have blown
the Kosovo conflict out of proportion and warned that airstrikes
would cause serious problems for the whole Balkan peninsula.
	   (adc)
</TEXT>
