<HEADLINE>
Lawrence Taylor arrested on drug charge
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   ST. PETE BEACH, Florida (AP) _ Former National Football League
star Lawrence Taylor was arrested Monday and charged with
possession of crack cocaine after making a purchase from an
undercover police officer.
	   Members of the St. Pete Beach Special Response Team entered his
hotel room shortly after 2 a.m. and arrested Taylor and Victoria
Corey, 41, who was identified as an employee of L.T. Enterprises.
	   Taylor, 39, of Saddle River, New Jersey, who played for the New
York Giants from 1981 to 1993, posted dlrs 15,500 bond and was
released from the Pinellas County Jail less than 12 hours later.
	   Police said Taylor, who helped the Giants to two Super Bowl
titles, purchased dlrs 50 worth of crack cocaine from the
undercover officer. He was arrested in his hotel room, where
officers found numerous items of drug paraphernalia in plain view.
</TEXT>
