<HEADLINE>
Two week walkout ends with pay raise agreement
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   ALGIERS, Algeria (AP) _ Striking employees at state-owned Air
Algerie reached an agreement with management Monday to end their
two-week-old walkout, officials said.
	   The accord, which the unions called ``a good compromise,'' calls
for a 15 percent pay raise, officials said. Management still vowed
to hold to a restructuring plan.
	   The walkout paralyzed domestic and international flights the
first week, though the airline managed to resume about half its
schedule since then.
