<SLUG> BC-Sports-Soccer-British Roundup </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Martin O'Neill's Leicester downs George Graham's Spurs
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   LEICESTER, England (AP) _ Muzzy Izzet smashed home a right-foot,
25-meter volley six minutes from the end as Leicester inflicted
Spurs first loss under new manager George Graham Monday and maybe
convinced its own manager, Martin O'Neill to stay.
	   With O'Neill targeted by Leeds to be its new manager after the
departure of Graham last month, the Leicester fans were worried
that a fourth defeat in nine games might mean they would lose the
inspirational former Northern Ireland international.
	   But the victory at Filbert Street pushed Leicester up four
places to 11th place while Spurs slipped to 14th.
	   Les Ferdinand fired in Darren Anderton's cross to put Spurs
ahead in the 14th minute but the Foxes leveled 13 minutes later
when Emile Heskey twisted round Swiss defender Ramon Vega to shoot
home.
	   Spurs manager Graham took David Ginola out of the game midway
through the second half after a poor display by the French forward.
	   Two minutes after Izzet's goal, Leicester's American
international 'keeper Kasey Keller, who had fumbled two crosses
earlier in the game, made a good save to keep out a header from
Chris Armstrong. Then the American stretched out an arm to fist
away a shot from the Spurs striker.
	   (rjm)	   
</TEXT>
