<SLUG> BC-Puerto Rico-Flash Flood Statement,0242 </SLUG>


<TEXT>

BULLETIN-IMMEDIATE BROADCAST REQUESTED URBAN AND SMALL STREAM FLOOD
ADVISORY NATIONAL WEATHER SERVICE SAN JUAN PR
432 PM AST MON OCT 19 1998

...THE NATIONAL WEATHER SERVICE IN SAN JUAN PR HAS ISSUED AN URBAN
AND SMALL STREAM FLOOD ADVISORY UNTIL 600 PM AST FOR THE WESTERN
MUNICIPALITY MAYAGUEZ...

AT 425 PM...DOPPLER RADAR SHOWED AN AREA OF THUNDERSTORMS WITH VERY
HEAVY RAIN ACROSS WESTERN PUERTO RICO OVER MAYAGUEZ...LAS MARIAS
AND MARICAO. THE THUNDERSTORMS HAVE CONTINUED TO REDEVELOP OVER THE
SAME AREA THROUGHOUT THE AFTERNOON. DOPPLER WEATHER RADAR
ESTIMATES 3 TO 4 INCHES OF RAINFALL HAS OCCURED OVER MAYAGUEZ DURING
THE PAST THREE HOURS. GROUNDS ACROSS THIS SECTION OF PUERTO RICO
REMAINED VERY WET FROM RECENT HEAVY RAINS. ALTHOUGH THERE WERE NO
REPORTS OF WIDESPREAD FLOODING...LOCALIZED STREAM..STREET AND ROAD
FLOODING WILL BE LIKELY ACROSS THIS AREA. THEREFORE AN URBAN AND
SMALL STREAM ADVISORY HAS BEEN ISSUED UNTIL 6 PM FOR MAYAGUEZ.

MOTORISTS AND PEDESTRIANS IN OR PASSING THROUGH THIS AREA SHOULD
AVOID CROSSING FLOODED ROADS...AND ALLOW EXTRA TIME TO REACH THEIR
DESTINATIONS. VISIBILITIES ARE GREATLY REDUCED IN HEAVY
RAIN. REMEMBER...CARS CAN EASILY STALL IN THE WATER AND BE CARRIED
AWAY IN ANY CURRENT. PEDESTRIANS ARE ALSO ADVISED TO STAY AWAY FROM
RISING CREEKS. AVOID STEEP TERRAIN WHERE MUDSLIDES ARE POSSIBLE.
	   
</TEXT>
