<SLUG> BC-Israel-Attacks-Box,0302 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Breakdown of major attacks on Israelis since June 1996
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; With Israel-Explosion, Mideast-Talks, Israel-Security Needs
 &UR; By The Associated Press &QC; 

<TEXT>
	   The breakdown of major attacks targeting Israelis since Prime
Minister Benjamin Netanyahu was elected in May 1996.
	   ____
	   _Oct. 19, 1998
	   A Palestinian man connected to the militant group Hamas throws
two grenades at a crowded outdoor bus station, wounding 64
Israelis.
	   _Oct. 13, 1998
	   Palestinian militants shoot to death an Israeli man and
critically wound a second as the two bathed in a spring near
Jerusalem.
	   _Oct. 9, 1998
	   A Palestinian man described as mentally unstable stabs to death
a female Israeli soldier near her home in the West Bank settlement
of Tomer.
	   _Sept. 24, 1998
	   A two-pound (one kilogram) bomb explodes behind a bus station
near the Hebrew University in Jerusalem, wounding an Israeli
soldier.
	   _Aug 27, 1998
	   A nail-studded bomb hidden in a trash can explodes wounding 21
people in Tel Aviv.
	   _Aug. 20 1998
	   A 63-year-old rabbi from the Jewish settlement of Hebron is
stabbed to death by an unknown assailant who broke into his mobile
home.
	   _May. 6, 1998
	   An Arab stabbed a Jewish seminary student to death as he walked
through Jerusalem's Old City on his way to pray at the Western
Wall.
	   _Sept.4, 1997
	   Three Palestinian suicide bombers blow themselves up in the Ben
Yehuda outdoor mall in Jerusalem killing 25 people.
	   _July 30, 1997
	   Two Palestinians detonate bombs in Jerusalem's Mahane Yehuda
market, killing themselves and 15 shoppers.
	   _March 21, 1997
	   A 28-year old Palestinian suicide bomber blows himself up in Tel
Aviv as Israelis prepared for the Purim Holiday. Three Israeli
women were killed and 47 other passersby injured.
</TEXT>
