<HEADLINE>
Three men killed in fight between soccer fans
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   KINGSTON, Jamaica (AP) _ Three men were shot to death during a
fight over a soccer game near Kingston, Jamaica, police reported
Monday.
	   They said the shooting occurred Sunday following a game in
Olympic Gardens, a neighborhood in the southeastern district of St.
Andrew.
	   The victims were identified as Devon DePass, 31; Dennison
Allison, 45; and Trevor Dixon, 24. They were shot repeatedly, and
their bodies were found on nearby Balmagie Avenue.
	   Amateur soccer games have led to deaths in Jamaica twice in the
last month. On Sept. 19, the manager of a community soccer team in
De La Vega City was charged with stabbing one of his players to
death.
	   There were no immediate details about the cause of the fight.
