<SLUG> BC-Sports-Ice Hockey-Bettman-Olympics,0145 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
NHL's participation in Olympics still up in the air
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   TORONTO (AP) _ The National Hockey League's participation in the
2002 Winter Olympics will depend on how negotiations go with
broadcast rights holder NBC, says league commissioner Gary Bettman.
	   ``The schedule has got to be put together so there is
considerable prime-time (TV) exposure for the U.S. and Canadian
teams because if we're not going to get substantial exposure for
our players ... it doesn't make sense for us to go,'' Bettman said
Monday.
	   In Nagano, Japan, CBS relegated hockey to the late-night show,
airing at either 11:35 p.m. or 12:35 a.m.
	   Bettman made the comments while attending the book launch of the
NHL-produced ``Total Hockey: The Official Encyclopedia of the
NHL.'' It was held at the Hockey Hall of Fame.
</TEXT>
