squadron of water-dropping planes, are blocking the flames of two
southern California wildfires. (FIRST RUN AFTER 0300)
----
TAIWAN: KOO - Chief envoy Koo Chen-fu is to brief reporters on his
five-day trip to China, which he has described as ``a good beginning
for better ties''. APTN expects to have highlights of the news
conference. (EXPECTED AFTER 0300)
----
TAIWAN: ZEB - Coverage of the devastation caused by Super Typhoon
Zeb which ravaged part of Asia over the weekend. Package shows
rescue workers probing for bodies after torrents of mud buried a
village near Taipei. (EXPECTED AFTER 0300)
----
JAPAN: MAHATHIR - Tuesday is the last day of Malaysian Prime
Minister Mahathir Mohamad's five-day visit to Japan, his first
overseas visit since a political crisis erupted in Malaysia last
month. APTN expects to have excerpts of a news conference Mahathir
held at the National Press Club of Japan. (EXPECTED AFTER 0300)
----
