officials on Monday to discuss the latest developments in Kosovo.
(WRAP FIRST RUN 0300 EUROPE)
----
BOSNIA: BODIES - Some 200 Muslims from all over eastern Bosnia came
to Tuzla on Monday to look for their missing relatives and friends
among 274 bodies recently found in a mass grave. (FIRST RUN)
----
GEORGIA: MUTINY - A military officer and several other leaders of
Monday's revolt in the former Soviet state of Georgia have been
charged with treason. President Eduard Shevardnadze said his country
had avoided a civil war with the surrender of the mutinous troops.
APTN has a wrap of the day's events. (FIRST RUN 2200 LATIN AMERICA)
----
CHINA: LABOUR - Chinese leaders on Monday opened a congress of the
government-backed Federation of Trade Unions, amid soaring
unemployment and worries about the unrest it could bring. (FIRST RUN
1955 ASIA PACIFIC LATE)
----
US: MICROSOFT 2 - APTN has a wrap of the opening day of Microsoft's
antitrust trial, which focused on a crucial meeting in June of 1995,
involving officials from Microsoft and Netscape. (FIRST RUN 1930
NORTH AMERICA LATE)
