<SLUG> BC-Sports-Soccer-Rosenborg,0121 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Sollied new coach in Gent
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   TRONDHEIM, Norway (AP) _ Because former Rosenborg coach Nils
Arne Eggen will return as of Jan. 1, present head coach Trond
Sollied signed two and a half year contract with Belgium Gent on
Monday.
	   A year ago Sollied was Eggen's assistant coach, but he did not
want to be an assistant to Eggen. Sollied led Rosenborg to the
seventh consecutive league title Sunday, and he will remain the
Rosenborg head coach until Jan. 1.
	   ``Gent is an exciting club, and it is a great challenge for me
as coach,'' Sollied told the Rosenborg website.
	   Gent is seventh in the Belgium league, seven points behind the
leader Lokeren after 10 rounds.
</TEXT>
