<SLUG> BC-Japan-Markets, 2nd Ld-Writethru </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Dollar, Tokyo stock prices inch higher at midday
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: UPDATES thruout with midday trading

<TEXT>
	   TOKYO (AP) _ The U.S. dollar edged up against the yen Tuesday
morning in lackluster trading, while Japanese stock prices moved
slightly higher after an overnight rise on Wall Street.
	   The dollar bought 114.78 yen at midday, up 0.06 yen from late
Monday in Tokyo and also above its New York level of 114.28 yen
late Monday.
	   The Nikkei Stock Average of 225 selected issues gained 15.12
points, or 0.11 percent, to 13,582.32 points to end the morning
session. On Monday, the Nikkei closed up 286.66 points, or 2.16
percent.
	   In currency trading, the dollar's strength against the German
mark led Japanese short-term players to buy back the U.S. currency
against the yen.
	   The dollar continued to benefit from speculation that the
Bundesbank, Germany's central bank, may lower interest rates at its
policy-setting meeting on Thursday, traders said.
	   But they said the dollar's direction against the yen remains
unclear.
	   On the stock market, an overnight gain on Wall Street encouraged
investors in Tokyo. The Dow rose 49.69 points _ or 0.6 percent _ to
finish Monday's session at 8,466.45.
	   Trading remained moderate in Tokyo, however, as many investors
took a wait-and-see attitude on expectations the government will
consider stimulus steps to lift Japan's moribund economy, dealers
said.
	   Kaoru Yosano, head of the Ministry of International Trade and
Industry, told reporters Monday that the government may come up
with a new set of economic stimulus measures next month.
	   The broader Tokyo Stock Price Index of all issues listed on the
first section was up 5.31 points, or 0.52 percent, to 1,028.23
points. The TOPIX closed up 16.24 points, or 1.61 percent, the day
before.
	   Meanwhile, the yield on the benchmark No. 203 10-year Japanese
government bond fell to 0.800 percent from Monday's finish of 0.815
percent, driving its price up to 108.96 yen from 108.82 yen.
 &UR; (js-km-dj) 	   
</TEXT>
