<SLUG> BC-Sports-Ice Hockey-NHL Roundup,0236 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Blackhawks edge Canadiens 2-1
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: will be updated &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   MONTREAL (AP) _ Eric Daze scored with 3:49 left in regulation to
lift the Chicago Blackhawks to a 2-1 victory over the Canadiens on
Monday night and earn their first win in Montreal since 1991.
	   Daze scored on a backhander off a rebound of Alexei Zhamnov's
long shot into an open side as goaltender Jose Theodore tried to
scramble back into the crease.
	   Rookie Daniel Cleary scored his first NHL goal in the first
period for Chicago (3-2-0), which had lost six games in a row in
Montreal since an 8-3 victory Feb. 6, 1991.
	   Vincent Damphousse scored on a power play 3:45 into the third
period for Montreal (2-2-1), which lost at home for the second time
in three nights.
 &UR; Predators 2, Maple Leafs 2
	   In Toronto, in Nashville's first and only appearance at Maple
Leaf Gardens, the expansion Predators battled the Toronto Maple
Leafs to a tie.
	   The Maple Leafs needed a goal from Fredrik Modin at 13:51 of the
second period to salvage the point.
	   Andrew Brunette scored and also assisted on Sergei Krivokrasov's
goal at 12:30 of the second that gave the Predators (1-2-1) a 2-1
lead.
	   Sergei Berezin gave Toronto (3-1-1) the initial lead in the
first period.
	   Mike Dunham played well for the Predators, stopping 30 shots as
Toronto outshot Nashville 32-25.
</TEXT>
