<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-SKorea-Hotel Fire </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
One foreign tourist dies in Seoul hotel fire
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   SEOUL, South Korea (AP) _ An electric short-circuit may have
started a fire that killed one foreign tourist and injured two
others at a Seoul hotel, police said Tuesday.
	   The fire broke out in a Turkish Airline office housed on the
second floor of the 19-story President Hotel in downtown Seoul
shortly before midnight Monday.
	   Hundreds of hotel guests scrambled to escape the fire and smoke,
with about 200 finding shelter on the roof of the building, police
said.
	   Fey Chung, a 46-year old Korean-American woman from Downey,
California, was later found dead outside the hotel. Police believe
she fell from her 11th floor room while trying to escape.
	   Two unidentified Japanese tourists were treated for smoke
inhalation and later released, police said. No other injuries were
reported.
</TEXT>
