<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Turkey-Tourist Bus Crash, 2nd-LD Writethru </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
British tourist bus crashes in Turkey; at least 7 dead, 35 injured
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: RECASTS and CLARIFIES in graf 4 that the 38 includes the
driver &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   IZMIR, Turkey (AP) _ A bus carrying British holiday-makers
collided with a car early Tuesday near this Aegean port, killing at
all five people in the car and two Britons on the bus and injuring
35 other bus passengers, the Anatolia news agency reported.
	   The tourists were traveling to Izmir's airport from Kusadasi,
and were on their way home to Britain from the resort.
	   According to Anatolia, the bus collided with a car at 2:20 a.m.
(1120 GMT), killing all five passengers in the car and two Britons.
	   A spokeswoman for the British holiday company Airtours, which
hired the bus, said the bus was carrying 38 people, including the
driver, when it collided head-on with a taxi.
	   The spokeswoman, speaking on customary condition of anonymity,
said hospital reports indicated that eight people were killed in
the crash _ three Britons and five Turkish nationals.
	   All passengers were taken to one of four local hospitals for any
needed treatment and at least one needed emergency surgery and was
undergoing an operation, the spokeswoman said.
	   ``Our rep was traveling in the front of the coach but she was
fine. She had chest pains but she was walking, talking and
organizing people after the crash, so it sounds as though it could
be a lot worse for people in the taxi,'' she said.
	   The identities of the victims were not immediately available.
Police was unavailable for comment.
	   (er)
</TEXT>
